  "setup": [
    {
      "comment": "Set TERM for proper color support in Neovim"
    },
    {
      "line": "export TERM=xterm-256color"
    },
    {
      "comment": "Prepare workspace"
    },
    {
      "line": "mkdir -p ~/vimfu && cd ~/vimfu"
    },
    {
      "line": "rm -f quest.py .quest.py.swp .quest.py.swo"
    },
    {
      "line": "rm -f ~/.local/state/nvim/swap/*quest.py*"
    },
    {
      "comment": "Create the demo file"
    },
    {
      "writeFile": "quest.py",
      "content": "hero = quest(\"dragon\", 99)\nloot = chest[\"gold\"] + 50\nmsg  = f\"Level {hero.xp}\""
    },
    {
      "line": "clear"
    },
    {
      "comment": "Launch nvim before recording"
    },
    {
      "line": "nvim quest.py"
    },
    {
      "waitForScreen": "All",
      "timeout": 30.0
    },
    {
      "ifScreen": "swap file",
      "thenKeys": "d"
    }
  ],
  "steps": [
    {
      "comment": "--- Title card ---"
    },
    {
      "overlay": "VimFu",
      "caption": "The Vim Grammar",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.5
    },
    {
      "comment": "--- Intro ---"
    },
    {
      "say": "Vim is a language. Every command is a verb plus a noun. Operator plus text object."
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.3
    },
    {
      "say": "You already know the verbs. D deletes. C changes. Y yanks. Greater-than indents.",
      "wait": false
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.3
    },
    {
      "say": "And you know the nouns. I W, a word. I quote, a string. I paren, a block.",
      "wait": false
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.5
    },
    {
      "comment": "--- Demo 1: ci\" — change inner quotes ---"
    },
    {
      "say": "C I quote. Change the string.",
      "wait": false
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.3
    },
    {
      "keys": "ci\"",
      "overlay": "change inner \""
    },
    {
      "type": "wyvern"
    },
    "escape",
    {
      "wait": 0.6
    },
    {
      "say": "Verb: change. Noun: inner quotes.",
      "wait": false
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.4
    },
    {
      "say": "Undo.",
      "wait": false
    },
    {
      "keys": "u"
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.4
    },
    {
      "comment": "--- Demo 2: di[ — delete inner brackets ---"
    },
    {
      "say": "D I bracket. Delete the array subscript.",
      "wait": false
    },
    {
      "keys": "j"
    },
    {
      "keys": "f["
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.3
    },
    {
      "keys": "di[",
      "overlay": "delete inner ["
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.6
    },
    {
      "say": "Verb: delete. Noun: inner brackets.",
      "wait": false
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.4
    },
    {
      "say": "Undo.",
      "wait": false
    },
    {
      "keys": "u"
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.4
    },
    {
      "comment": "--- Demo 3: yi( — yank inner parens ---"
    },
    {
      "say": "Y I paren. Yank the function arguments.",
      "wait": false
    },
    {
      "keys": "gg"
    },
    {
      "keys": "0"
    },
    {
      "keys": "f("
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.3
    },
    {
      "keys": "yi(",
      "overlay": "yank inner ("
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.6
    },
    {
      "say": "Verb: yank. Noun: inner parens. Copied to register.",
      "wait": false
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.4
    },
    {
      "comment": "--- Demo 4: >iw — indent the word? No — >ip indent a paragraph ---"
    },
    {
      "say": "Even indent is a verb. Greater-than I P. Indent the paragraph.",
      "wait": false
    },
    {
      "keys": "gg"
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.3
    },
    {
      "keys": ">ip",
      "overlay": "indent paragraph"
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.6
    },
    {
      "say": "Every verb works with every noun. That's the power of the Vim grammar.",
      "wait": false
    },
    {
      "wait": 0.5
    },
    {
      "comment": "--- Wrap up ---"
    },
    {
      "say": "Learn one new verb — it works with every text object. Learn one new noun — every operator works with it. The combinations multiply."
    },
    {
      "wait": 1.0
    }
  ],
